                               <div class="panel-heading clearfix"><h4 class="panel-title" style="text-align: center"><strong>Joe Ferguson</strong></div><img src="no oinpvm[o" class="img-responsive"/><div class="list-group">
                               <div class="list-group-item">
                               <h4 class="list-group-item-heading">Mentor</h4><h4 class="list-group-item-heading">First year with the team</h4></div><div class="list-group-item">
                               <p class="list-group-item-text">Mr. Ferguson has begun his first season with the robotics program at DHS. He has helped guide members of the business and marketing departments as well as add leadership training to the team captains. His hobbies include watching Boston Celtics games, wearing Boston Celtics merchandise, and dreaming of trade scenarios in which Boston Celtics GM Danny Ainge could improve the team. Away from the court Mr. Ferguson likes to wear sweaters in the Winter, T- shirts in the Summer, and baseball caps in the Fall and Spring. His favorite movie of all time is Predator, directed by John McTiernan, and starring two future United States Governors.  He is excited to be apart of such a great program and can't wait to take on the world this season with the team.</p>
